Program: Outlook
Title: 18/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00t6kjv
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 19 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, David Scheffer talks about the challenges he faced as America's first ambassador-at-large for war crimes issues. His book is called All The Missing Souls, published by Princeton University Press. Also, the story of Boris, a young Ukrainian sent to an old people's home after being labelled 'incapacited', and Tatjana Makarova, one of those who helped him find freedom and a new life. And in our Edible City series, how a Swede in London conjures up memories of childhood picnics. Show less